# Release Notes – v0.3.2

## Summary
This release focuses on improving the reliability and resilience of the Utilities Display by addressing sensor conversion warnings, improving startup behavior, and reducing unnecessary processing during Home Assistant reconnects.

The user experience, layout, and touch interface remain unchanged.

---

## Fixed

### Home Assistant Sensor Reliability
- Fixed warnings caused by `sensor.smart_meter_electricity_cost_this_month` temporarily becoming unavailable.
- Fixed warnings caused by `sensor.water_cost_monthly_with_base` temporarily becoming unavailable.
- Improved handling of missing sensor values to prevent invalid display updates.

### Ecobee Climate Integration
- Fixed intermittent warnings when Ecobee thermostat attributes temporarily returned `None` during startup or reconnection.
- Improved fallback behavior when target temperature values are unavailable.

### ESPHome Stability
- Reduced the likelihood of display update issues caused by temporary Home Assistant disconnects.
- Improved resilience during Home Assistant restarts and entity reloads.

---

## Improvements

- Enhanced overall stability of the Utilities Display package.
- Improved handling of unexpected or unavailable entity states.
- Reduced unnecessary redraw activity to help minimize ESPHome timing warnings.
- Improved recovery behavior after reconnect events.

---

## User Interface

### No Visual Changes
- All layouts remain unchanged.
- Home, Electric, Water, Weather, and Climate pages retain their existing appearance.
- Touch zones and navigation behavior remain unchanged.
- Existing functionality and workflows are preserved.

---

## Notes

- Gas values continue to use placeholder / demonstration data.
- This release is recommended for all users running previous **v0.3.x** versions.
- Existing local ESPHome configurations only require updating the GitHub package commit reference and reinstalling the firmware.

---

## Upgrade Instructions

1. Update the GitHub package to **v0.3.2**.
2. Update the package commit hash in your local Box-3 ESPHome configuration.
3. Recompile and install the updated firmware on the ESP32-S3 Box.

---

This release builds upon the stable v0.3.x foundation by prioritizing reliability and graceful handling of temporary Home Assistant entity availability issues without altering the established user experience.
